caption: Rasoi is awesome! Fantastic Indian cuisine (best in the STL Metro) served with care. I highly recommend.

Also, definitely no point in ordering garlic cheese bread from some pizza chain when you can just order the garlic cheese naan from Rasoi.

I ordered Veg Chettinad Curry and Garlic Nan.  Being a south indian expect the Veg Chettinad Curry in typical south Indian Chettinad Style, rather the dish was so disappointing no curry and taste and simply bland and all i can see only vegetables soaked in coconut based sauce.  I don't understand why you add yeast or baking soda to bring the fluffyness.  Why can't you make Garlic nan with simple all purpose flour without any yeast or baking soda.  It tastes like an American bread.  It was so disappointing to visit an Indian Restaurant and not to have a good Indian food.

I just got two pieces of tamarind seeds in it and thought it was meat, and that just ruined everything for me at that point. I could not eat any further. The meat was really good. It was well done, soft and tender. I have to appreciate it because it's hard to get the meet right. The mushroom biriyani was also ok.  Howevert was still water dripping from the mushrooms when I squeezed. I am not sure that is how it's supposed to be, because it was the first time we tried.  The quantity was great. And it's totally worth the price. Overall our experience was ok but could be great if it wasn't for the lamb biriyani. I hope you take this review in a positive way.

Absolutely fantastic. Now that we've gotten that out of the way...  Rasoi is the best Indian food I've had in St. Louis. They have a decently expansive menu, and everything I've had there is great. Their lunch buffet includes the usual suspects, but also has some surprise dishes like Bombay Aloo and Chettinad chicken. Even the standards like tandoori chicken and Tikka masala are very well executed. The chutneys are well balanced and a nice addition to the buffet as well as necessary components to their delicious samosas. The kheer could use a touch more spice, but it's creamy and satisfying. If you're in the neighborhood, stop in and give Rasoi a whirl. You won't be disappointed.

Update: Went back with my mom, so just two Indians this time, and the spice level on the vindaloo was fantastic, much spicier than last time. The food was just as delicious as the first time otherwise. The service this time was definitely friendlier too. Fantastic experience, upping my rating to a 5.  Original: My current favorite Indian restaurant in Saint Louis. The food was tasty and all the dishes our table tried had distinct and delicious flavors which seems to be a real problem at a lot of other places.  We tried the vindaloo, Tikka masala, karahi chicken, and rogan josh all of which were delicious. The naan was also the best that I've had in the area by far. The tandoori chicken and samosa were both just alright. The tandoori chicken didn't come with any charred veggies which was odd and the samosas were so not greasy it almost seemed baked rather than fried. Also the potatoes in the samosa were lacking a bit of salt.  I do also wish they would up the spice level a bit though at least for dishes like the vindaloo. We specifically asked for it to be spicy and it came out very mild. Not sure if that was due to being with American friends so it was more geared towards an American palate.  My other issues were that the place is a bit pricey for the portion sizes, and the service was just okay. The servers did well enough but they weren't very friendly.  But overall I was happy with the experience and will definitely be coming back!

A week in advance I had made reservations to have dinner with 45 people at Rasoi. The staff knowing we had 45 people, there were 4 people still left to be seated.  (The room wasn’t even big enough to fit that many people, yet accepted the reservation.) But we had asked for an extra table, but the lady owner said no we can only give you chairs. That was not the only problem, she wanted 6 people to be seated at a 4 person table. How were we supposed to eat comfortably??? We asked if we could have a table in the dinning room. Her answer was no because it was reserved. She said, “all of you guys have no sense to talk.” What does she mean?? We are the customers and your the person that is supposed to satisfy us with a wonderful dinner experience. But instead you talk extremely rude to us saying we were being rude to you and saying that we insulted you in front of your employees? But in reality you insulted us and yourself!! This will be our last time at Rasoi and I’m so glad that all of us walked out on you and you loss your business in front of all your other paying customers who were dinning in there. Definitely don’t recommend this place. Go to India’s Palace to get a welcoming customer service because they made us feel welcomed after we had no clue where to go eat without a reservation!
